============================================================
Example 1: In Mask - Keep Only Specific Fields
============================================================
Filters a data model to keep only the specified fields.

Original fields: thinking, answer
After in_mask(['answer']): ['answer']

============================================================
Example 2: Out Mask - Remove Specific Fields
============================================================
Removes specified fields from a data model.

Original fields: thinking, answer
After out_mask(['thinking']): ['answer']

============================================================
Example 3: Prefix - Add Prefix to Field Names
============================================================
Renames all fields by adding a prefix.

Original fields: answer
After prefix('original_'): ['original__answer']

============================================================
Example 4: Suffix - Add Suffix to Field Names
============================================================
Renames all fields by adding a suffix.

Original fields: answer
After suffix('_draft'): ['answer__draft']

============================================================
Example 5: Factorize - Group Similar Fields
============================================================
Groups similar fields (answer, answer_1, answer_2) into a list.

After concat: answer, answer_1, answer_2
After factorize: ['answers']
  answers has 3 items

============================================================
Example 6: Pattern Masking - Regex-based Field Filtering
============================================================
Use regex patterns instead of explicit key lists.

Original fields: thinking, answer
After in_mask(pattern='answer$'): ['answer']

============================================================
Example 7: Concat Function with Custom Naming
============================================================
Using function form allows custom names for operations.

Concat function allows custom naming for better traceability
